Cataloguing in Publication:  A New Programme of Pre-Publication Cataloguingin the United States of America, with Comments on some Similar Programmes.AClapp, Verner W.
   The cataloguing in source experiment carried out by the United States Library of Congress ended in 1959.. Studies on the feasibility of a new pre-publication cataloguing programme were undertaken and on 1 July 1971 a newcataloguing in publication programmes were started.. Other programmes forpre-publication cataloguing, namely in Brazil and the Union of Soviet SocialistRepublics, are described..